<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">How Painful is Brazilian Waxing?</h2>

<div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <p class="mb-4">
    Everyone has a different pain threshold, but our esthetician can reduce pain and discomfort by getting wax to the right temperature. It should be hot enough to melt not warm enough to hurt your skin. The experienced esthetician will have mind-body techniques such as breathing suggestions and other ways to calm the pain receptors.
  </p>
  <p>
    There is also an expert gesture to tear off the wax in a swift motion. If done quickly and effectively, this part of the process causes brief and minimal pain.
  </p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">Difference Between a Brazilian & Bikini Wax</h2>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
  <div>
    <img 
      src="/images/6358773dfa2fa42351f2e029_bad5dd22-73c2-4151-af44-9623a61de5f0_difference-between-brazilian-and-bikini-wax.jpeg"
      alt="Difference between Brazilian and bikini wax"
      class="w-full h-48 object-cover rounded-lg mb-4"
    />
  </div>
  <div>
    <p class="mb-4">
      You can also choose to use a bikini full wax. The bikini full waxing procedure removes the hair from around the mons pubis area. The mons pubis area covers the lower abdomen and extends to the labia. The process does not include the rear area.
    </p>
    <p>
      When you select the Brazilian wax method, you can tell your esthetician whether you want full coverage or want some hair to remain. For example, some women keep a small triangle, a small strip, or a square shape.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">The Brazilian Waxing Process in Scottsdale</h2>

<div class="mb-8">
  <img 
    src="/images/6358773dfa2fa42351f2e029_1682453305760-1IACFQ520VPMLAMVJAJW_how-is-brazilian-wax-done.jpeg"
    alt="How Brazilian wax is done"
    class="w-full h-64 object-cover rounded-lg mb-4"
  />
  <p class="mb-4">
    Here is what you can expect with your Brazilian wax session. Additionally, the wax temperature should remain comfortable. Our estheticians understand the art involved with using the appropriate temperature.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: #7B2D8E;">Preparing for Your Appointment</h3>

<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
  <ul class="space-y-3">
    <li class="flex items-start">
      <span class="font-bold mr-2" style="color: #7B2D8E;">1.</span>
      <span>Take a warm shower before your Brazilian wax session. It will help to open up the pores and make it easier for the wax to adhere to the hair.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start">
      <span class="font-bold mr-2" style="color: #7B2D8E;">2.</span>
      <span>Exfoliate the area before Brazilian waxing. Exfoliating helps remove dead skin cells and dirt, which can otherwise lead to irritation or discomfort during Brazilian waxing.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start">
      <span class="font-bold mr-2" style="color: #7B2D8E;">3.</span>
      <span>Don't use any creams or lotions before Brazilian waxing. It will help ensure that the wax sticks to the hair and not your skin.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start">
      <span class="font-bold mr-2" style="color: #7B2D8E;">4.</span>
      <span>Trim any pubic hairs before coming in for your session. It will keep all the hair even in length, which can minimize pain during Brazilian waxing.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start">
      <span class="font-bold mr-2" style="color: #7B2D8E;">5.</span>
      <span>You should also make sure you have enough hair to wax. Check to see if you have at least ¼ inch of growth. Checking this will ensure that the wax can adhere to the hair.</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
    Using these tips will help reduce pain and discomfort as we work to create an enjoyable experience.
  </p>
</div>

